        "title": "fix(cron): validate Telegram delivery target is numeric chat ID",
        "body": "fix(cron): validate Telegram delivery target to match runtime contract\n\n## Summary\n\n- **Problem:** The cron dashboard does not validate Telegram announce 'To' targets before saving. Invalid targets (e.g. random text) are forwarded to runtime delivery, which silently fails.\n- **Fix:** Add save-time validation that accepts Telegram runtime target forms: numeric chat IDs, @username, t.me links, telegram: prefixed targets, and topic-qualified targets. Add missing English i18n key and inline error rendering.\n- **Out of scope:** No changes to Telegram runtime delivery, outbound delivery, or channel authorization.\n\n## Linked context\n\nCloses #90467\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n- **Behavior or issue addressed:** Cron dashboard accepts invalid Telegram announce targets without validation. Valid targets like @username and t.me links are rejected by overly narrow numeric-only validation.\n- **Real environment tested:** Linux (NewStartOS V4.4.2-ZTE), Node.js v24.13.1, OpenClaw latest main (commit 5c46da06), local checkout with the patch applied.\n- **Exact steps or command run after this patch:** Ran `node --import tsx proof-91448.mjs` which directly exercises the `validateCronForm` function with various Telegram target inputs to verify the validation logic.\n- **Evidence after fix:**\n```\n$ node --import tsx proof-91448.mjs\n\n=== PR #91448: Telegram Delivery Target Validation Proof ===\n\nTesting isValidTelegramTarget function from ui/src/ui/controllers/cron.ts\n\n✅ numeric chat ID: \"123456\" => valid (expected: valid)\n✅ negative numeric chat ID: \"-1001234567890\" => valid (expected: valid)\n✅ @username handle: \"@username\" => valid (expected: valid)\n✅ t.me link: \"t.me/username\" => valid (expected: valid)\n✅ https t.me link: \"https://t.me/username\" => valid (expected: valid)\n✅ telegram: prefix: \"telegram:123456\" => valid (expected: valid)\n✅ tg: prefix: \"tg:123456\" => valid (expected: valid)\n✅ topic-qualified target: \"123456:topic:789\" => valid (expected: valid)\n✅ random text with spaces: \"random text\" => invalid (expected: invalid)\n✅ short username (< 5 chars): \"abc\" => invalid (expected: invalid)\n✅ username with @ in middle: \"user@name\" => invalid (expected: invalid)\n✅ username with space: \"user name\" => invalid (expected: invalid)\n\n=== Results ===\nPassed: 12/12\nFailed: 0/12\n\n✅ All Telegram target validation tests passed!\n```\n- **Observed result after fix:** The `validateCronForm` function correctly validates Telegram delivery targets against the runtime contract. Valid targets (numeric IDs, @username, t.me links, telegram:/tg: prefixes, topic-qualified targets) are accepted. Invalid targets (random text, short usernames, usernames with invalid characters) are rejected with clear error messages.\n- **What was not tested:** Live Telegram bot delivery (requires bot credentials). Live cron dashboard UI interaction.\n\n## Tests and validation\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run ui/src/ui/controllers/cron.test.ts` — 48/48 passed\n- 5 new test cases for Telegram target validation\n- English i18n key `cron.errors.telegramChatIdRequired` added\n- Inline error rendering with aria attributes added\n- No CHANGELOG.md edits\n\n## Risk checklist\n\n- userVisible: Yes (cron dashboard validation changes, error messages shown)\n- configEnvMigration: No\n- securityAuthNetwork: No\n- Mitigation: Validation mirrors runtime Telegram target contract from `extensions/telegram/src/targets.ts`\n\n## Current review state\n\n- Pre-existing CI failure: `build-artifacts` / Check Control UI i18n fails because `chat.ts` lines 2469-2470 have untranslated \"Dismiss Talk error\" string. This is NOT in this PR's diff — it exists on main.",
